Questions:
What is the primary objective of the DXC006 clinical trial?
A) To evaluate the long-term effects of DXC006 on cardiovascular health;
B) To assess the impact of DXC006 on cognitive function in patients with solid tumors;
C) To determine the safety and tolerability of DXC006, establish the Maximum Tolerated Dose (MTD) and Dose Limiting Toxicity (DLT), and recommend a dose for phase II trials;
D) To compare the efficacy of DXC006 with standard chemotherapy treatments.

Correct answer: C

Who will have access to your personal medical records for the purpose of monitoring the study, according to the consent form?
A) Only the study doctor and the patient themselves;
B) Drug regulatory authorities, ethics committees, study center staff, and representatives of the sponsor;
C) All hospital staff and the general public;
D) Only the patient's family members and friends.

Correct answer: B
